author: CNN
description:
The Justice Department on Wednesday said it has uncovered over a million more documents potentially related to the Jeffrey Epstein case and may need “a few more weeks” to process and release them to the public. 

The department made the revelation in a post on X, saying the the US Attorney for the Southern District of New York and the FBI had informed the department of the new documents.

00:00 Breaking news report on newly discovered files related to Jeffrey Epstein 
00:25 CNN crime and justice correspondent reports on newly discovered documents 
03:46 Ranking Democrat from the House Oversight Committee responds 
04:30 CNN Senior White House reporter live from West Palm Beach, Florida 

 #JeffreyEpstein #EpsteinFiles #News
title: DOJ says it found a million more docs potentially related to Epstein

author: CNN
description: Advent calendars are becoming about more than just chocolate. As the Christmas tradition is projected to become a billion dollar industry, according to market research firm MarketIntelo, influencers and creators are sharing some of their most extravagant countdown.
title: This old school holiday tradition is taking over the internet

author: CNN
description:
Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky signaled new willingness to make concessions on several key negotiating points that have threatened to stall a nascent peace process with Moscow, effectively putting the ball in Russia’s court. 

In an unusually candid and wide-ranging meeting with reporters Tuesday, Zelensky gave new details about a 20-point plan that he described as “a foundational document on ending the war, a political document between us, America, Europe, and the Russians.”

00:00 Live report from CNN correspondent in London on Ukraine peace negotiations 
03:15 Report on two police officers killed in a Moscow car bombing 
04:50 Pope Leo speaks about the need for peace in Ukraine 

 #VolodymyrZelensky #Ukraine #News
title: Ukraine’s Zelensky offers peace concessions – and puts the ball in Putin’s court

author: CNN
description:
A new lawsuit filed in Washington, DC’s federal court challenges the Kennedy Center board of trustees’ move to add President Donald Trump’s name to the cultural institution. 

Rep. Joyce Beatty, an Ohio Democrat and an ex-officio trustee of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, is bringing the lawsuit. She alleges a recent vote by the Center’s board of trustees to add Trump’s name went beyond the authority given to the board by Congress. 

 

00:00 Democratic lawmaker explains her lawsuit challenging Trump’s name being added to the Kennedy Center 
02:12 Legal expert weighs in on the Kennedy Center controversy 
06:00 Former federal prosecutor says the Kennedy Center name change violates the law

#KennedyCenter #DonaldTrump  #News
title: New lawsuit challenges Trump’s name on Kennedy Center

author: CNN
description:
The city of Bethlehem in the occupied West Bank is buzzing with Christmas festivities for the first time in three years as Palestinians express cautious optimism amid the ceasefire between Israel and Hamas. CNN's Matthew Chance reports. 

#CNN #News #Bethlehem
title: Bethlehem celebrates first Christmas in three years

author: CNN
description: As Ukraine faces a growing manpower crisis, some Ukrainian men are fleeing the fighting and attempting to evade draft. CNN's Chief International Correspondent Clarissa Ward travels to Romania, where some are risking their lives crossing the Carpathian Mountains to escape the country. #cnn #ukraine
title: Ukrainian men risking death to avoid the frontline

description: President Donald Trump slammed the late night hosts of ABC, NBC, and CBS in a series of Truth Social posts. Trump also said that any networks that are negative towards the GOP should have their licenses terminated. #cnn #trump
title: Trump targets TV networks in late night Truth Social posts

author: CNN
description: Video taken at an H-E-B grocery store in Burleson, Texas, shows a store employee offering free groceries to customers after she said there were technical problems with the registers. #cnn #news #heb #texas #christmas
title: Free groceries offered to customers after register glitch

author: CNN
description: North Korea has opened new luxury hotels near the Chinese border. But with foreign tourism still tightly restricted, questions remain over who is actually staying in them. CNN's Will Ripley reports. #cnn #news #northkorea #pyongyang #resorts
title: Who’s staying in North Korea’s luxury hotels?

author: CNN
description: Two people are dead and others are missing after a fire and explosion tore into a nursing home in Bristol, Pennsylvania. According to Pennsylvania Gov. Josh Shapiro, the cause of the explosion remains under investigation, but officials’ preliminary belief is that it was a gas leak. #cnn #news
title: Nursing home explosion kills at least 2 in Pennsylvania

author: CNN
description: Political and climate activist Greta Thunberg has been arrested in London for protesting in support of hunger strikers linked to Palestine Action, a group designated as a terrorist organization by the United Kingdom.
title: Greta Thunberg arrested at pro-Palestinian protest

author: CNN
description: China is developing a controversial hydropower system in a remote region of the Himalayas. Beijing has been tight-lipped on details of what it has called a "project of the century.” CNN's Simone McCarthy breaks down how the plan might take shape. #cnn #news #china #hydropower
title: China's secretive hydropower mega-project

author: CNN
description: The Vatican’s Christmas Nativity scenes go beyond tradition, aiming to convey a present-day message of Christmas. The main display in St. Peter’s Square is joined by more than 100 Nativity scenes from countries around the world, as the Vatican prepares for Pope Leo’s first Christmas since his election. CNN's Christopher Lamb reports. #cnn #news
title: Pope Leo’s first Christmas brings a powerful message

author: CNN
description: CNN's Ryan Young tours a real-life replica of the White House in Atlanta, complete with an oval office, a Lincoln bedroom, and a Truman-inspired balcony. It is currently on the market for $35 million. #cnn #cnnnews
title: Inside a $35 million White House replica that could be yours
